	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000983_0001"/><!--pb/@n='8r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">27<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> March</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I have made 
<lb/>a fair attempt to 
<lb/>get on in the way 
<lb/>of dictating from 
<lb/>my journal. <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi>
<lb/>Loysdon</persName> writes very 
<lb/>nicely and I am 
<lb/>satisfied with his 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000983_0002"/><!--pb/@n='8v'--> 
<lb/>abilities but I 
<lb/>find that I cannot 
<lb/>succeed the fault 
<lb/>being entirely in 
<lb/>myself. I feel 
<lb/>quite unable to 
<lb/>dictate continuously 
<lb/>or give a connected 
<lb/>narrative without 
<lb/>seeing the preceding 
<lb/>parts of the sentence<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I am sorry I 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000983_0003"/><!--pb/@n='9r'--> 
<lb/>have given you 
<lb/>so much trouble 
<lb/><del type="strikethrough">and beg you to pay 
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> L</persName> for today.</del></p>
<lb/><p>I shall go on 
<lb/>as usual slow 
<lb/>though that way 
<lb/>is unless you 
<lb/>think otherwise<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>Believe me &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I have paid him the 
<lb/>sum of 7/6<reg>.</reg></p>
			
</div>
